commitResults.messageTitle: Refactored the code to have initDuke() and terminateDuke() commands.
commitResults.messageBody: Purpose of this is separation of concerns: different functions deal with different parts of the Duke code.

commitResults.messageTitle: Added the runDuke() method. Removed the ASCII art for Duke as it is not part of the Level 1 expected out.
commitResults.messageBody: Note that in the future, should the ASCII art be necessary, it can be copied from the original GitHub repo, or obtained from an older commit.

commitResults.messageTitle: Edited runDuke() method to handle addition of input and listing of input.
commitResults.messageBody: All the input is stored in an ArrayList called storedInput (instance variable of Duke)

commitResults.messageTitle: Added DukeException class and error-handling code

commitResults.messageBody: Updated tests in text-ui-test to test for deletion functionality as well. The tasks were always stored in an ArrayList, so the current implementation also satisfied A-Collections

commitResults.messageTitle: Implemented saving functionality
commitResults.messageBody: All saving functionality, along with the transition between an ArrayList<Task> and the string storage format in a .txt file is encapsulated within the Storage class.

commitResults.messageTitle: Implemented DukeDate class to recognise dates in a specific format.
commitResults.messageBody: Currently, the date format is in the form dd/mm/yyyy hh:mm. Note that all functionality associated with date parsing and date printing is to be done by the DukeDate class

commitResults.messageTitle: Made some minor deletions of unnecessary imports
Fixed bug regarding printing of date format.
commitResults.messageBody: Bug was due to calling of getSaveFormat() method in parent class Task. When being saved, all tasks (todos, events, deadlines) were being saved as Todos.
